posts.raw_content:
Tried filing my taxes for the first time after getting married in early April as married filing jointly and got rejected because I didn't have an accompanied 1095-A form. That form is exclusively for those that have participated in the 'healthcare marketplace" aka Obamacare -- neither of us (myself or my wife) have ever applied or utilized Obamacare as we've had employer supplied insurance. 

My wife called up the Obamacare marketplace number and they confirmed it was opened with her SSN and her maiden name (even though her SSN is associated with her now married name). She inquired about what info is needed to open or apply for this stuff and all that is needed was name and SSN, no validation of anything, no photo ID, nothing.

Now we have been told we have to wait 30 to 45 days for the "investigation", hope they deem it to be fraudulent, and then have a corrected 1095-A form.

I'm convinced this is federal level Minnesota fraud that people are popping up "insurance" agencies, aiding criminals in fraudulently opening Obamacare policies, billing the government under these policies, and getting tons of money and\free healthcare\procedures -- it makes total sense why the left is so hell-bent on ensuring it stays around 

Anyone else experience this type of identity theft? Anyone the navigated this specific issue with filing taxes and getting IRS rejections due to identity theft with "Obamacare marketplace"? I'm convinced it should be dug into similar to Nick Shirley and the older gentleman Mike that was with him

The reps with Obamacare gave 3 establishments and the doctors\providers that were utilized during the fraud for my wife and the insurance companies utilized from the "marketplace"
